# Resume Example Style Guide

This guide ensures consistency, ATS-friendliness, and high educational value across all resume examples in this repository.

Our mission:  
**Help job seekers build modern, ATS-optimized, future-skills resumes ‚Äî especially in AI-augmented careers.**

---

## üéØ Purpose of This Style Guide
All resume examples in this repo must:

- Be **ATS-compatible**
- Show **realistic and ethical experience**
- Favor **skills + measurable accomplishments**
- Teach job seekers **what good looks like**
- Reflect **current & emerging industry demands** (AI, automation, cloud, security, data, product, etc.)
- Use **clear, professional language**
- Follow a **consistent structure**

This is not a random template repo ‚Äî it's a **trusted learning resource**.

---

## ‚úÖ Resume Format Requirements

| Category | Rules |
|---|---|
Layout | Single-column only (no designs that break ATS)  
Font Style | Clean & readable (e.g., Arial, Calibri, Inter, Roboto, SF Pro)  
Font Size | 10‚Äì12pt body, 14‚Äì18pt headers  
Sections | Must include key resume sections (see below)  
Icons, Tables, Graphics | ‚ùå Avoid ‚Äî they break ATS  
Length | Prefer 1 page, max 2 pages  
File Format (examples) | Provided as PNG previews + Markdown content  

### Required Sections in Every Example

- **Name + Role Title**
- **Contact / LinkedIn / Portfolio (no personal data in repo)**
- **Professional Summary**
- **Skills (grouped logically)**
- **Projects / Internship / Coursework**
- **Work Experience (if exists)**
- **Education**
- **Certifications (optional but encouraged)**
- **Tools & Technologies**

---

## üß† Writing Style

| Guideline | Example |
|---|---|
Use action verbs | Designed, built, automated, trained, deployed  
Quantify when possible | Improved accuracy by 12%, automated 30+ hours/week  
Prioritize clarity | ‚úÖ Built an LLM chatbot for FAQs  
No fluff/buzz | ‚ùå Passionate, hardworking, eager to learn  
Use real tools | Python, SQL, Git, Docker, FastAPI, Jupyter, LangChain  
Avoid vague claims | ‚ùå Expert in AI ‚Äî ‚úÖ Built RAG chatbot w/ embeddings  

### Tone & Language

- Professional, but student-friendly
- No hype language (‚Äúrockstar‚Äù, ‚Äúninja‚Äù)
- Focus on **outcomes & capability**
- Avoid jargon unless necessary

---

## üéì Projects Section Rules

Every resume example must include **2‚Äì4 projects** with:

- Project name
- Short problem statement
- Solution summary
- Tech stack
- *Measurable outcomes* (even if simulated but realistic)

Example:

> **RAG-based College Support Assistant**  
> Built a Q&A bot using LangChain + FAISS for college FAQs.  
> Improved response accuracy to 92% on test set; reduced staff load.  
> *Tech*: Python, OpenAI API, LangChain, Streamlit, FAISS

---

## üõ°Ô∏è Ethics

### ‚úÖ Good
- Realistic student / fresher projects
- Ethical AI use cases
- Honest capabilities
- Skills aligned to industry demand

### ‚ùå Not allowed
- Fake company experience
- Plagiarized content
- Competitor templates
- Personal resumes containing private info

---

## üîß Technical Skills That Should Appear Frequently

Since this repo focuses on **AI-era roles**, examples often include:

| Category | Skills / Tools |
|---|---|
AI & ML | Python, NumPy, Pandas, scikit-learn, OpenAI, LangChain  
Data | SQL, Excel, Tableau/Power BI  
Cloud | AWS / GCP / Azure basics  
Dev | Git, GitHub, VS Code  
MLOps | Docker, CI/CD basics, model monitoring basics  
Security | Basic cyber hygiene, IAM  
Product & QA | User research, test plans, prompt testing  

---

## üìê Bullets Format Example

Every bullet should follow:

**Action + Tool + Result**

